Police have launched a man hunt for an AK-47 wielding gang that descended upon Chakama trading center in Chakama, Makongeni sub-county of Kilifi county, firing indiscriminately at the locals, injuring five people before kidnapping a 23 year old volunteer from Africa Milele Onlus, an NGO operating in the area. The injured largely young boys sustained gun shot wounds on their neck, thighs and eyes and are currently in stable condition at the Malindi sub-county offices. The reason, and the identity of the attackers are yet to be established.  